sentence: The most common herbicide used was Herbicide Orange, more commonly referred to as Agent Orange: a fifty-fifty mixture of two herbicides 2,4-Dichlorophenoxyacetic acid (2,4-dichlorophenoxyacetic acid) and 2,4,5-Trichlorophenoxyacetic acid (2,4,5-trichlorophenoxyacetic acid) manufactured for the U.S. Department of Defense primarily by Monsanto Corporation and Dow Chemical.
